  "abstract": "The use of molecular markers has been shown to be a\r\npowerful approach for the genetic dissection andmanipulation\r\nof many traits of importance in agriculture. However, their full\r\nimpact, especially in breeding, is yet to be realized. This is due\r\nto a number of limitations such as the time and resources\r\nrequired to discover a large number of polymorphic markers\r\nfor a species, requirements for sequence information for\r\nmarker development, and the cost and time for scoring the\r\nmarkers (average per datapoint cost of overUS$1.00).\r\nWith the advent of Restriction Fragment.................",
